The paper uses machine learning techniques to predict wind pressures on tall buildings, indicating a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) also suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the study involves the optimization of wind tunnel testing, which could fall under the category of computational engineering (cs.CE).
